The script compares the parameter names and values in a set of INI files.
It accepts two directory paths: the source directory and the target directory.
It iterates through the source files and compares them with corresponding files in the target directory.
For each parameter, it checks if the value in the source file matches the value in the target file.
If a mismatch is found, it displays the filenames, the mismatched parameter, and the source and target values.
The script helps identify differing parameter values between INI files.
It is useful for configuration file analysis and troubleshooting.
Ensure the source and target directories contain the INI files you want to compare.
Run the script with ./compare_ini.sh <source_directory_path> <target_directory_path>.
Review the output to identify parameter mismatches between the source and target files.

./compare_ini.sh <source_directory_path> <target_directory_path>
